<h2>Ongoing Legal Support for Your Business</h2>
<p>Running a business requires more than just formation documents. From day-to-day contract review to major transitions like buying, selling, or dissolving a business, our attorneys provide legal guidance in maintaining businesses, preparing and reviewing agreements, and dissolution of businesses.</p>
<h2>Our Business Legal Services</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Contract Drafting & Review</strong> — We prepare and review business agreements, vendor contracts, non-compete agreements, and other critical documents.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Purchases & Sales</strong> — We guide buyers and sellers through due diligence, asset purchase agreements, and closing.</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance</strong> — We help businesses maintain compliance with Pennsylvania regulations and corporate governance requirements.</li>
    <li><strong>Dispute Resolution</strong> — We assist with partner disputes, contract disagreements, and other business conflicts.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Dissolution</strong> — When it's time to wind down, we handle the legal process of closing a business properly.</li>
    <li><strong>Succession Planning</strong> — We help family-owned businesses create effective succession and transition plans to preserve the business across generations.</li>
</ul>
